                     <section>
                        <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
                        <p>Now that we’ve walked you through all the steps of writing a cover letter, let’s summarize everything we’ve learned:</p>
                        <ul>
                           <li>A cover letter is a <strong>250 - 400 word document</strong> that convinces the hiring manager of your competence.</li>
                           <li>A cover letter goes in your job application <strong>alongside your resume.</strong></li>
                           <li>Your introduction to the cover letter should <strong style="background-color: rgb(255, 212, 59);">grab the hiring manager’s attention</strong> and&nbsp;keep it all the way until the conclusion.</li>
                           <li>There are 2 main topics you need to include in your cover letter: <strong>why you’re the perfect candidate for the job</strong> &amp; <strong>why you’re passionate about working in the company you’re applying to</strong>.</li>
                           <li>Most of the content of your cover letter should be <strong>factual</strong>, without any fluff or generalizations.</li>
                        </ul>
                        
